wikipedia_page.main: Eliot Callis (born 8 November 1994, in Doncaster) is a Northern first-class cricketer active since 2014 who plays for Yorkshire. He is a right-handed batsman and a right-arm leg break bowler. He played for Bedfordshire in the 2016 Minor Counties Championship. Callis toured Australia in 2017/18 to play for Kyabram cricket club who at the time were leading the club championship.
